contentrichtext.text: '''Hebe''' may refer to: *[[Hebe (mythology)]], the goddess of youth in Greek mythology *[[Hebe (genus)|''Hebe'' (genus)]], a genus of plants native to New Zealand *[[Hebe (Marvel Comics)]], a comics character in the Marvel Comics universe *[[6 Hebe]], a main-belt asteroid *[[Hebe Haven]] or Pak Sha Wan, a harbor in Hong Kong *[[Hebe Society]], a New Zealand botanical organisation *Hebe, a [[South Devon Railway Dido class]] steam locomotive *''Hebe'', a sculpture by [[Antonio Canova]] * Cousin Hebe, a character in Gilbert and Sullivan's ''[[H.M.S. Pinafore]]'' * a slang term for [[Hebrews|Hebrew]] or [[Jews|Jew]] ==Ships== *''Hebe'', a French frigate captured by the British Royal Navy in 1782 and used as the basis for their [[Leda class frigate]]s *[[Hebe (ship)|''Hebe'' (ship)]], a ship wrecked near Tasmania in 1808 * [[Hebe (brig)]], a brig built in 1861 *{{USS|Hebe|SP-966}}, a United States Navy patrol boat in commission from 1917 to 1918 ==People== *[[Hebe de Bonafini]], Argentine activist, born in 1928 *[[Hebe Camargo]], gone Brazilian television presenter *[[Hebe Tien]] Fu-chen, member of the Taiwanese girl group S.H.E {{disambig}}
